
Overview of noun devastation

The noun devastation has 5 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                  
1. devastation, desolation -- (the state of being decayed or destroyed)
2. devastation -- (the feeling of being confounded or overwhelmed; "her departure left him in utter devastation")
3. devastation, desolation -- (an event that results in total destruction)
4. ravaging, devastation -- (plundering with excessive damage and destruction)
5. destruction, devastation -- (the termination of something by causing so much damage to it that it cannot be repaired or no longer exists)
